<p>Easterlin, R. A. (1974). Dose economic growth improve the human lot? Some empirical evidence. In Nations and households in economic growth: Essays in honor of Moses Abramovitz (pp.89-125).New york : Academic Press. </p>
<p>Elizabeth, W. D., Daniel, T. G., &amp; Timothy, D. W.(2001) .If money doesn't make you happy, then you probably aren’t spending it right. Journal of Consumer Psychology, 21(2). </p>
<p>Emmons, R.A. (1986). Personal strivings: An approach to personality and subjective well-being. Journal of Personality and Social Psychology, 51(5). </p>
<p>Gilbert , D. T., Killingsworth, M. A., Eyre, R. N., &amp; Wilson, T. D. (2009).The surprising power of neighborly advice. Science, 323. </p>
<p>Srivastava, A., Locke E A., Bartol, K. M. (2001).Money and subjective well-being: It’s not the money, it’s the motives. Journal of Personality and Social Psychology, 80(6). </p>
